import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data['group'].value_counts()
    ax = group_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e', '#2ca02c'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Group')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of groups in the dataset?')
    for i, v in enumerate(group_counts):
        ax.text(i - 0.1, v + 0.5, str(v))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data['group'].value_counts(normalize=True)
    labels = group_counts.index
    sizes = group_counts.values
    colors = ['yellowgreen', 'gold', 'lightskyblue']
    plt.pie(sizes, labels=labels, colors=colors, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    plt.axis('equal')
    plt.legend(title="Groups", loc="center left", bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    plt.title("What is the most common group in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data.groupby('group')['person'].count()
    person_counts = data.groupby('person')['group'].count()
    groups = group_counts.index.tolist()
    people = person_counts.index.tolist()
    group_counts = group_counts.tolist()
    person_counts = person_counts.tolist()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(groups, group_counts, label='Group Count')
    ax.bar(groups, person_counts, label='Person Count')
    ax.set_xlabel('Group')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of people in each group?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    unique_persons = data.groupby('group')['person'].nunique()
    unique_persons.plot(kind='barh', color='green')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unique people in each group?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Number of unique people')
    plt.ylabel('Group')
    for i, v in enumerate(unique_persons):
        plt.text(v + 0.1, i - 0.1, str(v), color='black', fontweight='bold')
    return plt

data = pd.read_csv('lookup_groups.csv')
chart = plot(data)
```
